  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Project Manager",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities</p>\n<p>Overall supervision of assigned projects, to ensure timely completion of projects,</p>\n<p>Within the approved budgets set by the Project Manager and the management.</p>\n<p>Plan and prepare all project micro and/or master program with indication of Critical Path to complete assigned projects in a timely manner.</p>\n<p>To liaise with all subcontractors, consultants and owners on project matters and to resolve all technical discrepancies and site issues.</p>\n<p>To supervise and ensure that acceptable workmanship and quality of projects are obtained to the management and consultants’ approval.</p>\n<p>To attend, prepare and report on project progress, milestones and targets during meetings.</p>\n<p>To organise and to chair regular site meetings with subcontractors, NSCs and suppliers.</p>\n<p>Any other adhoc projects and duties as assigned by management.</p>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<p>Minimum Diploma Holder in Civil Engineering &amp; Construction</p>\n<p>Minimum 5 years relevant experience in civil, structural &amp; architectural work</p>\n<p>( Preferred Work Experience in Semi Detached House )</p>\n<p>Literacy in Microsoft Excel, Words, Powerpoint. Knowledge in Autocad &amp; Microsoft Project has added advantage</p>\n<p><br></p>",
